Project Description: End-to-End Data Pipeline for Licensing, Violations & Payments (ADLS + Snowflake)

Blob Storage name: https://<storage-account>.dfs.core.windows.net/rawdata/raw/

https://licdatadldev01.dfs.core.windows.net/rawdata/raw/

How to get tenant id : Azure Portal → Microsoft Entra ID → Overview → Tenant ID. Snowflake’s Azure integration requires this tenant ID.

Snowflake’s Azure storage integration for external stages uses 
TYPE = EXTERNAL_STAGE, STORAGE_PROVIDER = 'AZURE', your Azure tenant ID, and allowed Azure locations. For Azure stages, 
Snowflake documents the azure://<account>.blob.core.windows.net/<container>/<path>/ style URL, including for ADLS Gen2-backed storage accounts.

Use Below For Snowflake Integratoin
CREATE OR REPLACE STORAGE INTEGRATION azure_adls_int
  TYPE = EXTERNAL_STAGE
  STORAGE_PROVIDER = 'AZURE'
  ENABLED = TRUE
  AZURE_TENANT_ID = '<your-tenant-id>'
  STORAGE_ALLOWED_LOCATIONS = ('azure://<your-storage-account>.blob.core.windows.net/rawdata/raw/');
